translation.en: -[screeching] -[howling]
[BTG] Curious allies, zebra and ostrich tolerate each other
translation.es: Curiosos aliados, las cebras y los avestruces se toleran

translation.en: to avoid hungry predators.
The zebra relies on the ostrich's height and huge eyes,
translation.es: La cebra depende de la altura y de los enormes ojos del avestruz,

translation.en: which are larger than an elephant's, to see hidden dangers,
translation.es: más grandes que los de un elefante, para ver los peligros ocultos,

translation.en: while the ostrich depends on the zebra's superb sense of smell.
translation.es: y el avestruz depende del sentido del olfato de la cebra.

translation.en: Easy, buddy.
Just a friendly ostrich casually probing your anus for fecal parasites.
translation.es: Soy un avestruz amigable buscando parásitos fecales en tu ano.

translation.en: -[Dietrich] Bees! -[braying]
Oh no. [screams]
[groans] Buttocks.
-[bees buzzing] -Hypodermic needles with wings.
They're gonna give me hepatitis!
-Bees can't give you hepatitis, Dietrich. -How do you know, Bonnie?
translation.es: - No pueden darte hepatitis. - ¿Cómo lo sabes, Bonnie?

translation.en: -I guess I don't. -Well, I-- [gasps]
-I hate nature so much right now. -[scoffs]
translation.es: Ahora mismo odio a la naturaleza.

translation.en: Dietrich, when I'm elbow-deep in a zebra's anus,
translation.es: Cuando estoy hasta el codo en el ano de una cebra,

translation.en: I need you to keep it down, okay?
Ten years as my field assistant, I'm surprised you don't know that.
translation.es: Diez años como asistente de campo, me sorprende que no lo sepas.

translation.en: I do know that,
but I've also seen hateful bees sting you so many times
translation.es: pero también vi a abejas picándote tantas veces

translation.en: your skin looked like pre-chewed gum.
translation.es: que tu piel parecía goma de mascar.

translation.en: Ha! That was such a great day.
[inhales deeply] Still not sure why you'd carry that photo around.
translation.es: No sé por qué tienes esa foto.

translation.en: I've got one too, Uncle B.
From when you brought a Tasmanian devil to my sixth birthday party.
translation.es: De cuando llevaste un demonio de Tasmania a mi cumpleaños.

translation.en: [BTG] Oh yes.
[laughs] Good times!
You really need to embrace nature's wonders and horrors.
translation.es: Debes aceptar las maravillas y los horrores de la naturaleza.

translation.en: Just try to be more like Bonnie.
But this is her first expedition. She should be more like me.
translation.es: Es su primera expedición. Ella debería ser como yo.

translation.en: [shrieks] I'm not vaccinated!
Don't worry! I've been prepping for this expedition my entire life.
translation.es: ¡No te preocupes! Me preparé toda la vida para esta expedición.

translation.en: I've got everything.
GPS, bug spray, tranquilizer gun, an apple--
translation.es: GPS, repelente, pistola tranquilizante, una manzana…

translation.en: No guns.
Incoming wounded!
Those animals!
-Keep your whiskers up, sunshine. -[tiger growls]
Lieutenant Greive,
did you bring a tiger to the medical tent again?
translation.es: ¿trajo un tigre a la tienda hospital de nuevo?

translation.en: It's an Indochinese tiger, sir. They're almost extinct.
translation.es: Es un tigre de Sumatra. Están casi extintos.

translation.en: Bah! Do you know how many signs I had to commission because of you?
translation.es: ¿Sabes cuántos carteles tuve que encargar por su culpa?

translation.en: That's my ex-wife, Linda. Can't be too careful.
translation.es: Es mi exesposa. No se puede ser demasiado cuidadoso.

translation.en: -[bombs exploding] -You're my best paratrooper commander
translation.es: Mire, es mi mejor comandante paracaidista

translation.en: and the only decent baritone in the officers' a cappella group,
translation.es: y el único barítono decente en nuestro grupo a capela,

translation.en: but you have to make a choice.
Are you gonna be part of this regiment, or are you gonna play with wild animals?
translation.es: ¿Será parte de este regimiento o jugará con animales salvajes?

translation.en: The animals need me more.
Ah, that Bradley Trevor Greive is a magnificent lunatic.
translation.es: Ese Bradley Trevor Greive es un lunático magnífico.

translation.en: How long do you think he can maintain that incredible physique?
translation.es: ¿Cuánto tiempo podrá mantener ese físico increíble?

translation.en: Um… You were saying?
[BTG] Rule number one of Greive expeditions.
translation.es: Regla número uno de expediciones Greive.

translation.en: If you need a gun to feel safe in the wild, you don't belong out here.
translation.es: Si necesitas un arma para sentirte seguro, no perteneces aquí.

translation.en: Stay home.
Wait, what?
I thought rule number one of Greive expeditions was never try to save you.
translation.es: Creí que la regla número uno era nunca intentar salvarte.

translation.en: Correct, you should never try to save me. There are two rule number ones.
translation.es: Correcto, nunca intentes salvarme. Hay dos reglas número uno.

translation.en: Excellent.
The last animals in a parasite census
translation.es: Los últimos en un censo de parásitos

translation.en: are always the most rewarding.
You two, stay here and, uh, practice your tweezer technique.
translation.es: Ustedes dos, quédense aquí y practiquen usar sus pinzas.

translation.en: Yes! Something in my comfort zone.
translation.es: ¡Sí! Algo en mi zona de confort.

translation.en: Watch and learn, Bonnie.
[scoffs] Oh my God.
Don't you get bored watching BTG do all the fun stuff?
translation.es: ¿No te aburres viéndolo hacer cosas divertidas?

translation.en: This feces is chock-full of amazing parasites.
translation.es: Estas heces están llenas de parásitos increíbles.

translation.en: Other than the birth of my daughter, this is the best day of my life.
translation.es: Aparte del nacimiento de mi hija, es el mejor día de mi vida.

translation.en: Um, my idea of fun is a little different.
translation.es: Mi idea de diversión es diferente.

translation.en: You ever play Mahjong?
So exciting!
I stay awake at night dreaming of chows, pongs, and kongs.
translation.es: Paso las noches despierto soñando con chows, pungs y kongs.

translation.en: Look, something's in those bushes.
-We should check it out. -Are you nuts?
Fine, I'll check it out.
Just stay here and practice your tweezering.
translation.es: Quédate aquí y practica con las pinzas.

translation.en: Listen to me.
Every field assistant BTG's ever had died a horrible death.
translation.es: Cada asistente de campo de B. T. G. ha muerto de manera horrible.

translation.en: I actually saw one get nature-murdered on my very first day.
translation.es: Vi a uno asesinado por la naturaleza en mi primer día.

translation.en: I was a free-spirited grad student with washboard abs and perfect skin
translation.es: Yo era una estudiante de espíritu libre con abdominales y piel perfecta

translation.en: on a research trip.
-[screaming] -BTG had plunged into the open sea
translation.es: B. T. G. se había sumergido

translation.en: to tag a shortfin mako shark with his field assistant, Ulrich.
translation.es: para marcar a un tiburón mako con su asistente, Ulrich.

translation.en: Shark monster!
-[grunts] -Are you done? Good.
We need to head back.
Ulrich's been attacked by a shark, but he should be…
translation.es: Un tiburón atacó a Ulrich, pero debería…

translation.en: Oh, that's not good.
Oh my God! Ulrich!
-[retches] -Did you just cough up a hot dog?
I don't chew properly when I'm stressed.
translation.es: No mastico bien cuando me estreso.

translation.en: Ah, no shame in that.
Sharks vomit up entire meals to distract larger sharks from eating them.
translation.es: Los tiburones vomitan comidas enteras para distraer a otros tiburones.

translation.en: Mmm! Wow. Dietrich, I have good news. Mmm!
You are my new field assistant.
translation.es: Eres mi nuevo asistente de campo.

translation.en: What? Me?
But I'm only here for three days for college credit.
translation.es: Pero solo estoy aquí por tres días.

translation.en: I don't wanna be a field zoologist.
translation.es: No quiero ser zoólogo de campo.

translation.en: I wanna be a zoology professor at UC Davis.
translation.es: Quiero ser profesor en la universidad.

translation.en: Mmm, don't worry, this is gonna be great for your career. [munches]
translation.es: No te preocupes, será genial para tu carrera.

translation.en: Or you'll die.
Either way, it's a step forward, so congratulations.
translation.es: Como sea, es un paso adelante, felicidades.

translation.en: Okay. [inhales deeply]
Let's tag another shark while there's still so much blood in the water.
translation.es: Marquemos otro tiburón mientras haya sangre en el agua.

translation.en: Oh, goodbye, Ulrich.
You were a great field assistant.
translation.es: Fuiste un gran asistente de campo.

translation.en: One of the best.
In you go!
That was ten years ago,
making me BTG's longest surviving field assistant by nine years and six months.
translation.es: así que duré nueve años y seis meses más que ningún otro asistente de campo.

translation.en: You know how I managed to survive all that time, Bonnie?
I never do anything.
Bonnie?
Oh, hello!
Aren't you a cute little furry thing?
Bonnie! Back to the jeep!
It's my lucky day!
Bonnie! Bonnie!
-Over here! -[snarling]
Crap!
No, no, no, no, no! [pants]
Help! The headlights won't turn on!
[grunts] Good thinking, Dietrich!
Bonnie, listen to me.
You need to stay with the herd to be protected. Loners get picked off.
translation.es: Debes quedarte con la manada. A los solitarios se los comen.

translation.en: I thought I saw danger. Turns out I was right.
translation.es: Creí ver peligro. Resulta que tenía razón.

translation.en: There were lions.
You're not in a classroom now. This is the wild.
translation.es: No estás en un salón de clases. Esta es la naturaleza.

translation.en: I need you to hang back, observe and learn.
Ugh! But you've been telling me that my entire life.
translation.es: Me has dicho eso toda mi vida.

translation.en: -Now can I go into the field with you? -[slurping]
No, Bonbon. [chuckling] You're too young. [slurping]
Now can I go into the field with you?
No, Bonnie, you need more training.
Now can I go into the field with you?
No, Bonnie! You're too…
Hang on.
Hello? Mrs. Peterson?
Yes, thanks for calling. I'm sorry, I've… I've got to take this.
translation.es: Gracias por llamar. Disculpa, tengo que atender.

translation.en: You're talking into a banana!
I'm a grown woman, Uncle B.
If you really want me to learn, you're gonna have to let me get hurt.
translation.es: Si quieres que aprenda, deberás dejar que me lastime.

translation.en: [BTG] So, I'm a little overprotective.
-[huffs] -It's an ambush!
Look at that bird! He's the brains of the operation.
translation.es: ¡Miren a ese pájaro! Es el cerebro de la operación.

translation.en: Sorry, big fella. That's just a cattle egret.
translation.es: Lo siento, amigo. Es solo una garza bueyera.

translation.en: The Cape buffalo tolerates the egret
translation.es: El búfalo cafre tolera a la garza

translation.en: because it eats parasites and insects off his skin.
translation.es: porque come parásitos e insectos de su piel.

translation.en: Easy meal for the bird, good hygiene for the buffalo.
translation.es: Comida fácil para el ave, buena higiene para el búfalo.

translation.en: I love animal friends that shouldn't be friends.
translation.es: Me encantan los amigos que no deberían ser amigos.

translation.en: One time, I saw a video of a bear who was friends with a duck.
translation.es: Una vez, vi un video de un oso amigo de un pato.

translation.en: Yeah, I saw that video.
I'm pretty sure those animals were drugged.
translation.es: Estoy seguro de que estaban sedados.

translation.en: -[groans] -Anyway, I wouldn't call them friends,
translation.es: De todos modos, no los llamaría amigos.

translation.en: more like a mutualistic relationship where each benefits from the other.
translation.es: Es una relación en la que cada uno se beneficia del otro.

translation.en: Blah, blah, blah. They're BFFs.
If it looks like a duck and sounds like a duck--
translation.es: Si parece un pato y suena a pato…

translation.en: Crows sound like ducks.
-Would you say that we're friends? -Not now, Dietrich. Look!
translation.es: - ¿Dirías que somos amigos? - Ahora no, Dietrich. ¡Mira!

translation.en: -[buffalo chuffing] -[BTG gasps] Black gold.
This is gonna be a parasite bonanza!
-[bellows gently] -Don't mind me.
All we need to find now is a mountain nyala,
the pride of Ethiopia.
Ah! There's nothing quite as invigorating as a good parasite census.
translation.es: No hay nada tan estimulante como un buen censo de parásitos.

translation.en: Have you ever tried recreational drugs? Because I have news for you.
translation.es: ¿Has probado drogas recreativas? No sabes lo que dices.

translation.en: Inappropriate uncle talk, Bonnie.
translation.es: No es apropiado para un tío.

translation.en: But, yes, I once licked a Sonoran Desert toad,
translation.es: Pero sí, una vez lamí un sapo del río Colorado,

translation.en: but this is better.
Big b-buffalo b-back-o!
-[jeep crashing] -Oh no! Uncle B!
Give it up, Bonnie.
BTG's dead.
You're a Greive,
and your initials are BTG, which means you can legally sign my paychecks,
translation.es: y tus iniciales son B. T. G. Puedes firmar mis cheques.

translation.en: and, also, that makes you next in line to lead the Greive expeditions, right?
translation.es: Y además eres la heredera de las expediciones Grieve, ¿no?

translation.en: Um… Yeah. Yes.
I… I guess so.
Well, congratulations, Dietrich, you're my new field assistant.
translation.es: Felicitaciones, Dietrich, eres mi nuevo asistente de campo.

translation.en: Wha… What? Me?
Oh God!
-Did I even graduate college? -Come on.
translation.es: - Ni sé si me gradué de la universidad. - Vamos.

translation.en: Uncle B! Uncle B!
Ah. Crap. There's no sign of him.
translation.es: Demonios. No hay señales de él.

translation.en: Uncle B!
Not dead yet.
Back off! I'm not being eaten alive beneath the jeep.
translation.es: ¡Atrás! No me comerán vivo debajo del jeep.

translation.en: That's what happened to my old field assistant, Bardrich.
translation.es: Eso le pasó a mi viejo asistente de campo, Bardrich.

translation.en: Fifty thousand social spiders working together
built that collective super web.
Their cooperation allows them to capture far larger prey
translation.es: Les permite capturar presas mucho más grandes

translation.en: than any single spider could ever dream of.
translation.es: de lo que cualquier araña podría soñar.

translation.en: Pretty cool, right, Bardrich?
I'm not Bardrich. My name's Emmerich.
translation.es: No soy Bardrich. Me llamo Emmerich.

translation.en: Oh, sorry. What happened to Bardrich?
translation.es: Lo siento. ¿Qué le pasó a Bardrich?

translation.en: -I love my job! I love my life! -[grunting ferociously]
translation.es: ¡Me encanta mi trabajo! ¡Me encanta mi vida!

translation.en: Oh, right.
Well, anyway, you get my point, right, Emmerich?
Wow, that's the quickest one yet.
-[cawing] -I refuse to be a Bardrich.
translation.es: Me niego a ser un Bardrich.

translation.en: For the last time, Dietrich,
there is no such thing as mountain crocodiles.
translation.es: los cocodrilos de montaña no existen.

translation.en: -Bonnie! -[Bonnie gasps]
Yes! I knew you weren't dead!
Or are you a zombie?
You just emerged from the earth, and your face is bloated and disgusting.
translation.es: Saliste de la tierra y tienes la cara hinchada y asquerosa.

translation.en: Thank God! Someone who actually knows something.
translation.es: ¡Gracias a Dios! Alguien que sabe algo.

translation.en: Are mountain crocodiles a thing?
In the Cardamom Mountains of Cambodia? Yes!
translation.es: Sí, en las Montañas de Cardamomo de Camboya.

translation.en: I knew it! I'm never listening to Bonnie again.
translation.es: ¡Lo sabía! No volveré a escuchar a Bonnie.

translation.en: [scoffs] Son of a…
-[wolves calling] -Uh-oh. Ethiopian wolves.
Here, put these on.
[Dietrich] Monkey suits?
It's finally happened. BTG's gone insane.
[BTG] Ethiopian wolves could eat young gelada monkeys,
translation.es: Los lobos etíopes podrían comer geladas jóvenes,

translation.en: but instead of fighting and getting hurt, they choose to hunt together.
translation.es: pero en lugar de pelear y lastimarse, eligen cazar juntos.

translation.en: The monkeys expose small rodents while digging up tubers and plant shoots.
translation.es: Los monos exponen roedores pequeños al desenterrar tubérculos y brotes.

translation.en: An easy meal for the wolves and added protection for the monkeys.
translation.es: Una comida fácil para los lobos y protección para los monos.

translation.en: -[snarling] -Classic mutualism.
You mean, animal friends that shouldn't be friends?
Sort of like… us?
Sure.
Trusted friends, temporary colleagues. Well, whatever.
translation.es: Amigos de confianza, colegas temporales. Como sea.

translation.en: Those wolves do not wanna be this far down the mountain.
translation.es: Esos lobos no quieren estar tan abajo de la montaña.

translation.en: -[animal growling] -Uh-oh. In fact…
Go ahead, lion. Finish what you started.
translation.es: Adelante, león. Termina lo que empezaste.

translation.en: [Bonnie] Uncle B!
No, Bonnie!
Rule number one!
Which rule number one?
-[groaning] Get up that tree! Now! -[growling]
[BTG] Back here, lions.
-I'm your main course! -[snarling]
[laughs] And probably dessert as well, if I'm being honest.
translation.es: Y el postre también, si soy honesto.

translation.en: Bonnie, this is your chance!
Escape while they feast on my marbled flesh and gristle!
translation.es: ¡Escapa mientras se dan un festín con mi carne!

translation.en: Carry on the Greive name. Make me proud.
translation.es: Defiende el nombre Greive. Hazme sentir orgulloso.

translation.en: No! No! No!
If we don't help you, we're not your field assistants.
translation.es: Si no te ayudamos, no somos tus asistentes,

translation.en: We're just parasites!
I'm not an Aldrich, or a Bardrich, or a Dietrich.
translation.es: No soy un Aldrich, ni un Bardrich, ni un Dietrich.

translation.en: -No offense, Dietrich. -Oh, none taken.
I have very high self-worth.
I'm breaking rule number one.
I'm still not gonna do anything.
Ooh, sorry!
Ah! I have to admit,
that was a brilliant zoological strategy, Bonbon.
translation.es: que fue una estrategia brillante, Bonbon.

translation.en: Thank God I went to an Ivy League school.
translation.es: Fui a una universidad de la Ivy League.

translation.en: If there's one thing I know how to do, it's kick the creeps where it hurts.
translation.es: Si hay algo que sé hacer, es darle su merecido a los bravucones.

translation.en: -[rustling] -Mountain crocs!
[BTG gasps] A magnificent mountain nyala.
[gasps] The final animal on the parasite census!
Know what, Bonnie? Why don't you take this one?
No way!
-[Bonnie] Ha-ha! Yes! -Are you sure she can handle this?
[inhales deeply] I'm sure. She's a Greive.
She's a BTG. This is in her blood.
translation.es: Es una B. T. G. Lo lleva en la sangre.

translation.en: [grunts] Crap!
I'm good.
Attagirl!
[sighing] Ah! I'm gonna be sad when one of you gets killed and eaten.
translation.es: Estaré triste cuando maten y coman a uno de ustedes.

translation.en: Mmm, hopefully in that order.
Oh, Mother.
Even animals that traditionally hunt alone can form unusual symbiotic partnerships…
translation.es: Incluso los animales que tradicionalmente cazan solos…

translation.en: -[Bonnie] Uncle B. Gold. -…with different species.
-Found your yearbook. -[BTG] Oh, is that gold, really?
What were you like in high school?
I was friends with a lot of kids from a lot of different backgrounds.
translation.es: Era amigo de niños de diferentes orígenes.

translation.en: And when I started exploring the world, those friendships paid off.
translation.es: Cuando comencé a explorar el mundo, esas amistades valieron la pena.

translation.en: I don't care about those people cliques anymore. I'm more of an animal person now.
translation.es: Ya no me importan los grupos. Me importan más los animales.

translation.en: But you gotta remember that, in nature, animals behave much like we did in high school.
translation.es: Pero en la naturaleza los animales se comportan como nosotros en la escuela.

translation.en: They have their own cliques. Like tortoises--
translation.es: Tienen sus grupos. Como las tortugas.

translation.en: -[Bonnie] Stoners. -[BTG] Correct.
Yaks? Jocks.
The meathead jocks are the ones in the gym just getting their beef on.
translation.es: Los atletas que se la pasan en el gimnasio.

translation.en: -[Bonnie] Yeah. -Wallabies?
-Like the track team? -[Bonnie] Oh, definitely. Porcupines?
translation.es: - ¿Atletas de pista? - Definitivamente. - ¿Puercoespines? - Son los súper vírgenes.

translation.en: [BTG] They're like the hardcore super virgins.
-[laughs] He's back! -Scorpions are goths.
-[BTG] Uh-huh. -Tarantulas, emo kids.
-What's the difference? Ah. -Eyeliner.
-Zebra, thespians. -[BTG] Drama club. Yeah.
translation.es: - Cebra, actores. - Club de teatro. Sí.

translation.en: Oh. Vulture?
A really mean principal, and he hates the kids,
translation.es: Un director muy malo que odia a los niños

translation.en: because he hates his life.
-Nature, high school, one and the same. -[Bonnie] Yeah.
translation.es: - La naturaleza es igual a la secundaria. - Sí.
